Package com.example.impostersyndrom.model

Class Mood

java.lang.Object
com.example.impostersyndrom.model.Mood
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Mood extends Object implements Serializable
The Mood class represents a mood entry in the application. It stores information about the user's emotional state, including: - Emotional state (e.g., happy, sad) - Emoji description - Timestamp - Color associated with the mood - Reason for the mood - Group context (e.g., alone, with others) - Optional image URL - User ID - Emoji drawable resource ID This class implements Serializable to allow Mood objects to be passed between activities.
Author:
Roshan Banisetti, Garrick, Eric Mo
